The article discusses a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on May 4, 2010. The briefing covers various topics, including the Times Square bomb suspect, the no-fly list, the BP oil spill, and the Supreme Court nomination process. Gibbs provides updates on the ongoing investigation into the Times Square bomb suspect and addresses concerns about the no-fly list and airport security. He also discusses the Obama administration's response to the BP oil spill and the potential lifting of the liability cap for BP. Finally, he addresses questions about the Supreme Court nomination process and the President's stance on immigration reform.